criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  8 to 17 years of age

          -  having lost one or both parent to AIDS (orphans) or are currently living with a
             HIV-positive parent (vulnerable children)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  children living in centralized care setting;

          -  known HIV-infection;

          -  physical illness and developmental disability (e.g., severe mental retardation) that
             prevent them from engaging routine daily activities;

          -  plan to permanently relocate outside of the province within a year.
